The paper deals with graph partitioning, which is a fundamental problem in computer science and falls under the category of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The problem involves finding a partition of the vertex set, which is a combinatorial optimization problem and can be categorized under discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper also discusses the expansion of subsets of vertices, which is a central concept in theoretical computer science and falls under the category of computational complexity (cs.CC). The problem of graph partitioning also has applications in computational geometry, which falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). Finally, the paper discusses the use of approximation algorithms, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT).
